betterquesting:10.desc:8:
Seems like cooling the exotic ingots are a far bigger issue than smelting them.

Luckily reinforcing some of the casings with your new materials allow you to inject exotic coolants to help capture the extreme heat in miniature tears of spacetime, so you can cool your ingots just a bit faster.

With the Subspace Cooling, you can allow the Vacuum Freezer to have Perfect Overclocks... for a cost.

Tier 1 will consume SpaceTime in liquid form at [warn]7500 L/s[/warn] and allow for 1 Perfect Overclock

[note]This is a very high but a static cost and it will be the same for each recipe that is being run. So definitely selectively cool your ingots. 

The faster those recipes are the more efficient the cost, so pick your balance.[/note]

The Infinity Cooled Casings replace the Frostproof casings, so no need to worry about breaking your setups.
